In <1993Mar23.170327.2611@vixvax.mgi.com> I replied:
> For the non-octal-heads, I'll recommend a 16-sider to generate one
> nibble per roll.  A permanent marker altering 10-16 to be A-F+0 also
> simplifies things a bit.  Available at a gaming store near you... 

In article <a_rubin.732991027@dsg4.dse.beckman.com>,
a_rubin@dsg4.dse.beckman.com (Arthur Rubin) followed up with:
> If this is serious, I would like to point out that 16-sided dice are NOT
> common in gaming stores -- if you really want to generate a nibble per
> roll, get a 20-sided die, relable 10-15 as A-F, and ignore 16-19.

Arthur is correct.  I finally bothered to check at home and we have d4,
d6, d8, d10, d12 and d20, but notably no d16s.  oops.  FWIW, I will add
that d20s are commonly labeled 1-20 or 0-9/0-9 (thus 20 -> 0). 
